source: cli/tests/cli_snapshot_tests.rs
expression: stdout
---
Transfer SOMA or USDC to one or more recipients

Usage: soma transfer [OPTIONS] <AMOUNT> <RECIPIENTS>...

Arguments:
  <AMOUNT>         Amount to send (in SOMA by default, or USDC with --usdc)
  <RECIPIENTS>...  Recipient address(es) or alias(es)

Options:
      --usdc                            Send USDC instead of SOMA
      --amounts <AMOUNTS>               Per-recipient amounts (comma-separated). Overrides the positional amount
      --coins <COINS>                   Input coin object IDs (comma-separated, auto-selected if not provided)
      --tx-digest                       Compute the transaction digest and print it out, but do not execute
      --simulate                        Perform a dry run (simulation) of the transaction, without executing it
      --serialize-unsigned-transaction  Serialize the unsigned transaction data (base64) instead of executing. Use with `soma tx execute-signed --tx-bytes <TX_BYTES>`
      --serialize-signed-transaction    Serialize the signed transaction data (base64) instead of executing. Use with `soma tx execute-combined-signed --signed-tx-bytes <SIGNED_TX_BYTES>`
      --json                            Output as JSON
  -h, --help                            Print help

EXAMPLES:
    soma transfer 10 0x1234...5678              # send 10 SOMA
    soma transfer 1.50 0xABC... --usdc          # send 1.50 USDC
    soma transfer 5 0xA... 0xB... 0xC...        # split 5 SOMA equally among 3 recipients
    soma transfer 0 0xA... 0xB... --amounts 3,2 # send 3 to first, 2 to second
    soma transfer 10 0xABC... --coins 0xC1,0xC2 # use specific input coins
